The paper focuses on Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) using LiDAR sensors, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework also involves handling different types of LiDAR, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for processing the LiDAR data. The paper also mentions the use of sparse pose graphs, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the proposed framework involves real-time mapping, which could involve control systems (cs.SY) for ensuring the system operates in real-time.
